BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jSxykyT9HSZ_vlzMPqVJM
SUMMARY:SP 101: Intro to Vera's Screen Print Studio
DTSTAMP:20260404T043958Z
DTSTART:20260409T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:This 2-hour\, comprehensive hands-on class teaches you all the 
	basics of screen printing at VERA’s screen printing studio: From hand-draw
	ing a stencil on transparency\, coating and burning a screen\, to pulling 
	your very first print! Get comfortable with Vera's shop layout\, equipment
	\, and culture. Learn techniques for creating screens\, terminology\, and 
	more to create 1-color projects in the print shop. Students will walk away
	 with the basic skills for screen printing 1-color paper prints\, and thei
	r own print of a special Vera design\, specific to the 101 class. This cla
	ss is a prerequisite for 200-level classes at VERA\, as well as access to 
	Open Sessions to work on your own projects in VERA’s screen printing studi
	o.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/sp-101-intro-to-vera-s
	-screen-print-studio/14809998/2026-04-08T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/sp-101-intro-to-vera-s-sc
	reen-print-studio/14809998/2026-04-08T00
LOCATION:Book-It Repertory Theatre\, 305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TN2F0FwB0i7RQse8jJLCP
SUMMARY:Tai Chi for Health and Balance
DTSTAMP:20260404T043958Z
DTSTART:20260409T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:Class Overview\n\nTai Chi is a health sustaining exercise and a
	 tool for improved body awareness. Practiced by the elderly for balance an
	d circulation and the young for relaxation and martial arts\, it is a wond
	erful holistic activity for all ages. We'll focus on learning the entire Y
	ang short form\, and you'll receive guidance in developing your own regula
	r practice at home.\n\nDuring this class\, you'll learn:\n\n-The Yang Tai 
	Chi short form\, which is comprised of 35 individual movements\n\n-Chi Kun
	g\, a warm-up exercise and relaxation activity with 18 movements\n\n-Eleme
	nts of Chinese Medical Philosophy\, such as Yin/Yang theory and Five Eleme
	nts transformation\n\n-the basics of Taoist philosophy\n\nLearning Objecti
	ves\n\nLearn basic warm-up stretches to improve your overall movement\n\nD
	iscover the Yang-style short form of Tai Chi\n\nPractice the Yang-style un
	der the direction of an expert instructor\n\nGain knowledge about the hist
	ory and background of Tai Chi\n\nWho Might Enjoy This Class?\n\nIndividual
	s seeking a low-impact exercise routine\n\nAnyone interested in improving 
	their coordination and balance\n\nPeople interested in developing their fo
